---
title: Dukkah-Crusted Salmon & Yoghurt with Veggie-Loaded Currant Couscous
description: You can truly throw just about anything into a couscous and watch the magic happen, but we’re putting on a real show tonight with a blushing slice of salmon, crusted in dukkah. Make sure not to miss our hidden trick with the currants (psst, they’re tossed in the couscous), they’re the closing act to go alongside the salmon.

*This recipe is under 650kcal per serving.*
